    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-18T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="348"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2266</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MJVA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-18T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Repeat to Tokyo your July 13, 4 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d348fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_280">p. 280</ref>, See also
                        the Chargé’s telegram of July 12, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_278">p. 278</ref>.</note> Please say to Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs that the American Government would view with regret any attempt by China
                    to take advantage of Russia’s present distress to regain control of the Chinese
                    Eastern Railway as reported in above-mentioned telegram. The American Government
                    fears such action now would arouse resentment in Russian people and defeat our
                    common desire to assist them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
